1
00:00:11,291 --> 00:00:14,583
Mr. Koyama,
you're being charged with fraud.

2
00:00:14,666 --> 00:00:16,000
Do you understand?

3
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,708
No, I don't, Detective.
I didn't do anything of the kind.

4
00:00:20,791 --> 00:00:24,208
You know the Yakuza can't stay at hotels,
right?

5
00:00:24,291 --> 00:00:25,958
You booked a hotel room for yourself,

6
00:00:26,041 --> 00:00:29,000
but Kiyoshi Kyogoku,
one of the leaders of the Fushimi-gumi,

7
00:00:29,083 --> 00:00:30,208
stayed there.

8
00:00:31,166 --> 00:00:35,750
There's video footage of the two of you
arriving at the hotel and checking in.

9
00:00:36,541 --> 00:00:38,041
It's pretty clear-cut.

10
00:00:38,125 --> 00:00:40,541
[inquisitive music playing]

11
00:00:40,625 --> 00:00:43,208
Oh, let me guess.

12
00:00:44,583 --> 00:00:47,041
Your attorney Mr. Kujo
told you to stay quiet?

13
00:00:48,041 --> 00:00:51,291
[Kujo] <i>The police wouldn't have arrested</i>
<i>you unless they had evidence.</i>

14
00:00:51,375 --> 00:00:53,208
But they'll need to prove
that you intended

15
00:00:53,291 --> 00:00:54,875
to let Mr. Kyogoku stay at the hotel,

16
00:00:54,958 --> 00:00:57,375
and to do that
they'll need you to confess.

17
00:00:57,458 --> 00:01:01,583
So if you remain silent,
it's unlikely you'll be prosecuted.

18
00:01:04,708 --> 00:01:06,708
All you have to do is
stay quiet for 20 days,

19
00:01:06,791 --> 00:01:07,791
and they'll cut you loose.

20
00:01:12,041 --> 00:01:15,333
You know Tonohata,
the driver for the call girls, right?

21
00:01:15,833 --> 00:01:20,000
He was kidnapped by someone
who burned his dick off with a stun gun.

22
00:01:21,583 --> 00:01:24,250
He thinks the owner, Kuga,
ordered it as punishment

23
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:26,375
for laying his hands on one of the girls,

24
00:01:26,458 --> 00:01:28,208
which sounds logical.

25
00:01:28,708 --> 00:01:31,833
So he retaliated
by setting Kuga's car on fire.

26
00:01:32,875 --> 00:01:35,625
Detective. What are you talking about?

27
00:01:35,708 --> 00:01:38,583
You know what I think? Do you?

28
00:01:39,166 --> 00:01:43,041
I think you asked your friend Kyogoku
to take care of Tonohata.

29
00:01:43,125 --> 00:01:45,958
Huh? Now, why would I do that?

30
00:01:46,458 --> 00:01:48,708
Because he sued you over Shizuku Pien
and won.

31
00:01:48,791 --> 00:01:52,250
He took one of your most profitable
porn stars away from you.

32
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:55,708
Detective,
I don't even know who that guy is.

33
00:02:00,250 --> 00:02:02,750
So, that's the way you wanna play this,
huh?

34
00:02:05,708 --> 00:02:06,583
[music fades]

35
00:02:06,666 --> 00:02:08,291
Remember Manami?

36
00:02:12,375 --> 00:02:13,958
Yeah, that's right.

37
00:02:14,916 --> 00:02:19,833
She was murdered ten years ago.
Supposedly by some kid.

38
00:02:20,958 --> 00:02:23,166
Thing is, she posted on social media

39
00:02:23,250 --> 00:02:24,958
that she was dating you.

40
00:02:27,916 --> 00:02:30,708
So I looked into you,
and you were running an escort agency

41
00:02:30,791 --> 00:02:31,750
ten years ago.

42
00:02:32,583 --> 00:02:35,333
You ran a business hooking up
so-called celebrities

43
00:02:35,416 --> 00:02:37,958
with wealthy CEOs looking for action,
right?

44
00:02:39,625 --> 00:02:42,625
Word is,
some of those girls were pretty young.

45
00:02:44,875 --> 00:02:46,333
Fact is, you were pimping out

46
00:02:46,416 --> 00:02:48,500
a bunch of little girls, weren't you?

47
00:02:50,375 --> 00:02:51,708
You're disgusting.

48
00:02:53,458 --> 00:02:57,458
Your client list had politicians
and high-level bureaucrats on it, huh?

49
00:02:58,583 --> 00:03:01,958
You were afraid Manami Ogawa
was going to tell on you,

50
00:03:02,041 --> 00:03:06,125
so to shut her up,
you ordered Kyogoku to kill her.

51
00:03:06,625 --> 00:03:07,875
[Koyama sighs]

52
00:03:08,833 --> 00:03:12,666
You know something?
You're really good at telling stories.

53
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:15,000
You should be a writer after you retire.

54
00:03:17,208 --> 00:03:18,666
I feel bad for Manami,

55
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:21,458
but isn't the guy who did it
already in jail?

56
00:03:21,541 --> 00:03:25,125
The case was solved.
What's the point of digging it up again?

57
00:03:28,625 --> 00:03:30,000
[bangs on table]

58
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:32,666
I'm on to you.

59
00:03:35,375 --> 00:03:38,083
I guarantee you,
it's only a matter of time.

60
00:03:49,666 --> 00:03:52,708
Oh, I get it.

61
00:03:53,916 --> 00:03:56,083
You don't look much alike.

62
00:03:57,666 --> 00:03:59,458
You know, Manami told me

63
00:03:59,541 --> 00:04:03,083
she refused to use the bathwater
after her father had used it

64
00:04:03,583 --> 00:04:06,375
because she was so disgusted by him.

65
00:04:07,333 --> 00:04:10,208
In my experience,
if a girl's grossed out by her father,

66
00:04:10,291 --> 00:04:13,208
it's because
they don't pay any attention to her.

67
00:04:13,291 --> 00:04:15,666
Don't pay any attention
to their wives either.

68
00:04:16,250 --> 00:04:18,291
The girl listens to them fight,
and soon enough,

69
00:04:18,375 --> 00:04:20,125
she starts to hate her dad.

70
00:04:20,208 --> 00:04:23,000
Koyama, you have a daughter, right?

71
00:04:23,083 --> 00:04:25,625
You must be having a hard time with her.

72
00:04:25,708 --> 00:04:28,708
You make a living exploiting
vulnerable women and girls.

73
00:04:28,791 --> 00:04:30,000
Of course, she hates your guts.

74
00:04:30,083 --> 00:04:32,166
You're making a lot of assumptions there.

75
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:36,875
Most of my employees are women,
and a lot of them have problems.

76
00:04:36,958 --> 00:04:37,958
I listen…

77
00:04:38,958 --> 00:04:41,500
To their grief, their pain, and suffering.

78
00:04:41,583 --> 00:04:45,333
I think the reason I'm so successful
is because I listen to women.

79
00:04:45,416 --> 00:04:49,750
I pay attention.
Especially to my daughter and my wife.

80
00:04:49,833 --> 00:04:51,958
- Fukami, get him out of here.
- [Fukami] Yes, sir.

81
00:04:52,458 --> 00:04:54,041
[upbeat music playing]

82
00:04:59,083 --> 00:05:00,125
Arashiyama.

83
00:05:02,083 --> 00:05:03,208
It's funny.

84
00:05:03,291 --> 00:05:06,083
You were always so obsessed
with catching criminals

85
00:05:06,166 --> 00:05:08,875
that you didn't even know
your own daughter.

86
00:05:16,291 --> 00:05:20,750
Manami was like…
a lot of girls who end up here, detective.

87
00:05:21,791 --> 00:05:25,875
She loved money and having sex,
so she combined the two.

88
00:05:25,958 --> 00:05:27,041
[music ends]

89
00:05:27,125 --> 00:05:29,583
She was a dirty little whore.

90
00:05:29,666 --> 00:05:30,583
[chuckles]

91
00:05:36,791 --> 00:05:38,250
Mr. Kujo,

92
00:05:38,333 --> 00:05:40,750
I finally figured out
why they hauled me in here,

93
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:42,833
and it's not for fraud either.

94
00:05:43,583 --> 00:05:44,541
[Kujo] What?

95
00:05:44,625 --> 00:05:48,000
Arashiyama is my ex-girlfriend's father.

96
00:05:48,083 --> 00:05:50,083
I never would have believed it.

97
00:05:51,750 --> 00:05:53,000
Is that so?

98
00:05:53,083 --> 00:05:56,250
So that explains why he arrested me
for this hotel thing,

99
00:05:56,333 --> 00:05:58,625
which is so stupid.

100
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:02,125
His daughter was raped and murdered,
so he's got something against me.

101
00:06:02,208 --> 00:06:03,625
What do I care?

102
00:06:04,250 --> 00:06:06,250
[laughs]

103
00:06:06,333 --> 00:06:07,708
[tense music playing]

104
00:06:07,791 --> 00:06:10,166
[Koyama] So anyway,
I'm about to lose 20 days of my life

105
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:12,500
because this detective's got a vendetta.

106
00:06:12,583 --> 00:06:14,666
He's a pain in the ass, but to be honest,

107
00:06:14,750 --> 00:06:17,458
his daughter was a bigger pain in the ass.

108
00:06:17,541 --> 00:06:20,208
She got herself knocked up
and said it was mine,

109
00:06:20,291 --> 00:06:21,666
so I made her have an abortion.

110
00:06:21,750 --> 00:06:23,916
That made her even worse.

111
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:26,583
She's still a fuckin' pain in my ass,
even dead.

112
00:06:26,666 --> 00:06:28,791
I can't stand the way you talk.

113
00:06:30,333 --> 00:06:31,208
But

114
00:06:32,916 --> 00:06:35,083
I'll do my best to represent you.

115
00:06:52,625 --> 00:06:54,625
[theme music playing]

116
00:07:21,041 --> 00:07:23,083
[woman] I don't know
what I would've done without you.

117
00:07:23,166 --> 00:07:24,708
Thank you, Mr. Kujo!

118
00:07:33,666 --> 00:07:35,541
Hi. I'm back. How's it going?

119
00:07:42,875 --> 00:07:44,166
[Kujo sighs]

120
00:07:46,125 --> 00:07:47,916
Hello? Mr. Kujo.

121
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:51,333
[Kujo] Hello, Mr. Karasuma.

122
00:07:51,416 --> 00:07:54,333
They say sighing like that
will drive away happiness.

123
00:07:55,916 --> 00:07:57,250
[Kujo] Sounds about right.

124
00:07:59,208 --> 00:08:00,833
What is it? Are you tired?

125
00:08:02,750 --> 00:08:04,291
[Kujo] Do I look tired?

126
00:08:05,583 --> 00:08:07,541
[Karasuma] A bit, yeah.

127
00:08:07,625 --> 00:08:09,833
How about I make you coffee for a change?

128
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:14,666
That would be great.

129
00:08:17,791 --> 00:08:18,958
[Karasuma] Mmm.

130
00:08:24,083 --> 00:08:26,041
My mom gave me this coffee.

131
00:08:27,625 --> 00:08:29,875
Keep it for yourself, then. It's a gift.

132
00:08:29,958 --> 00:08:33,500
Well, I don't have a grinder,
so I'd have to use yours anyway.

133
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:36,291
In that case, thank you.

134
00:08:38,750 --> 00:08:40,875
But she said this is a roast
my dad used to like.

135
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:46,083
I was a kid, though,
so I've never tried it.

136
00:08:46,583 --> 00:08:49,041
So, now I'm excited to see
what it tastes like.

137
00:08:50,791 --> 00:08:52,708
You're usually the one
who makes me coffee,

138
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:54,208
so I just copied you.

139
00:08:54,291 --> 00:08:55,208
I hope it's good.

140
00:08:55,291 --> 00:08:56,666
[Kujo] I'm sure it is.

141
00:08:58,458 --> 00:08:59,958
[sipping]

142
00:09:01,833 --> 00:09:03,708
Mmm. It's delicious.

143
00:09:03,791 --> 00:09:05,041
[chuckles]

144
00:09:09,041 --> 00:09:10,083
[Karasuma sighs]

145
00:09:10,166 --> 00:09:12,083
It's nice up here on the roof.

146
00:09:14,125 --> 00:09:16,041
[Kujo] Yeah. It is.

147
00:09:21,916 --> 00:09:23,583
[Karasuma] You look like yourself again.

148
00:09:25,416 --> 00:09:26,250
[Kujo] Like myself?

149
00:09:27,250 --> 00:09:29,083
When you came back
from visiting Mr. Koyama,

150
00:09:29,166 --> 00:09:30,875
you had this look I've never seen before.

151
00:09:30,958 --> 00:09:31,875
[chuckles]

152
00:09:33,750 --> 00:09:36,250
[Karasuma] You know better than anyone
what will happen to you

153
00:09:36,333 --> 00:09:38,166
if you continue to defend Koyama.

154
00:09:43,291 --> 00:09:45,000
[cell phone buzzes]

155
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,291
Hello. Kujo speaking.

156
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:56,708
[Rino] <i>Hi, Daddy. How are you?</i>

157
00:09:57,208 --> 00:09:58,041
Rino?

158
00:09:59,666 --> 00:10:01,791
[Rino] <i>Mommy bought me a cell phone.</i>

159
00:10:02,750 --> 00:10:03,916
[chuckles]

160
00:10:04,000 --> 00:10:07,125
That's wonderful.
How're you doing, sweetheart?

161
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:08,750
[Rino] <i>I'm good.</i>

162
00:10:09,500 --> 00:10:12,708
<i>Well, have a good day. Goodbye, Daddy.</i>

163
00:10:13,333 --> 00:10:14,166
[line clicks]

164
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:22,458
[Karasuma] Your daughter's six, right?

165
00:10:22,541 --> 00:10:23,375
Yeah.

166
00:10:23,458 --> 00:10:25,958
Then she must be using
a cell phone for kids.

167
00:10:27,000 --> 00:10:28,166
Yeah, probably.

168
00:10:30,083 --> 00:10:31,625
What about it?

169
00:10:31,708 --> 00:10:34,041
It's just that…
when they're set up for kids,

170
00:10:34,125 --> 00:10:35,875
they can only call certain numbers.

171
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:41,375
So that means your ex-wife must have
put your number in Rino's phone.

172
00:10:45,541 --> 00:10:48,291
NEW CONTACT
RINO

173
00:10:48,375 --> 00:10:50,541
There's hope
you'll get visitation after all.

174
00:10:55,500 --> 00:10:57,500
[indistinct background chatter]

175
00:11:08,625 --> 00:11:10,041
Koyama said

176
00:11:10,750 --> 00:11:13,958
Manami liked selling her body,
called her a dirty whore.

177
00:11:14,041 --> 00:11:15,000
[Miho chuckles]

178
00:11:15,083 --> 00:11:16,916
Koyashan said that?

179
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:19,875
And I didn't say anything back,
just sat there.

180
00:11:20,500 --> 00:11:22,541
I'm a lousy excuse for a father.

181
00:11:23,625 --> 00:11:26,791
I can't believe she ended up
being used like that.

182
00:11:28,083 --> 00:11:31,416
Girls can be easily impressed
by confident creeps.

183
00:11:32,375 --> 00:11:36,708
They're naive and fooled by people
who know exactly what to say.

184
00:11:36,791 --> 00:11:41,125
And even if it's a bullshit compliment
from a loser, they're desperate for it.

185
00:11:42,416 --> 00:11:44,000
Is that how it is?

186
00:11:44,916 --> 00:11:48,833
I'm starting to realize how little
I actually knew about my own daughter.

187
00:11:49,375 --> 00:11:51,541
You really feel like
you don't know anything about her?

188
00:11:51,625 --> 00:11:54,583
Yeah. Like what kind of food did she like?

189
00:11:54,666 --> 00:11:57,125
What kind of things did she like doing?

190
00:11:57,208 --> 00:11:58,500
I don't know anything.

191
00:11:58,583 --> 00:12:00,083
Well, she liked KARA.

192
00:12:00,166 --> 00:12:02,375
Kara? What is that? A restaurant?

193
00:12:02,458 --> 00:12:04,958
[laughs]

194
00:12:05,041 --> 00:12:06,500
No, it's K-pop. [chuckles]

195
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:10,333
We were really into K-pop.
I was into Girls' Generation.

196
00:12:10,416 --> 00:12:13,208
We used to go and sing karaoke
all night long.

197
00:12:14,250 --> 00:12:16,083
I had no idea she was even a singer.

198
00:12:16,166 --> 00:12:17,000
[Miho] Mm-hmm.

199
00:12:18,291 --> 00:12:19,916
She was really good too.

200
00:12:21,291 --> 00:12:23,041
Especially Hikaru Utada's songs.

201
00:12:25,250 --> 00:12:28,000
Sometimes she'd cry when she sang.

202
00:12:30,500 --> 00:12:32,666
I remember it so clearly still.

203
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:37,125
She was thoughtful and caring.

204
00:12:39,041 --> 00:12:40,041
And cute too.

205
00:12:45,500 --> 00:12:47,000
[chuckles]

206
00:12:49,458 --> 00:12:51,500
You two really are related.

207
00:12:52,041 --> 00:12:53,083
What?

208
00:12:53,166 --> 00:12:56,833
Manami loved shichimi togarashi
on her udon soup too.

209
00:12:57,625 --> 00:12:59,791
She piled it on, just like you.

210
00:13:01,708 --> 00:13:02,958
[chuckles]

211
00:13:04,083 --> 00:13:06,625
[melancholy music playing]

212
00:13:09,375 --> 00:13:10,583
Ms. Miho,

213
00:13:12,958 --> 00:13:18,583
I want to thank you
for remembering Manami the way you do.

214
00:13:21,791 --> 00:13:22,708
Thank you.

215
00:13:28,416 --> 00:13:30,291
[little girl] Daddy, can I have this?

216
00:13:32,083 --> 00:13:32,916
[man] Hmm…

217
00:13:33,625 --> 00:13:36,833
- What is it? Where did you find it?
- [little girl] Over there.

218
00:13:36,916 --> 00:13:39,833
Come on.
Let's go ask Mommy if it's okay. Okay?

219
00:13:44,250 --> 00:13:48,125
Daddy, can I have this?

220
00:13:50,000 --> 00:13:50,958
No, Manami.

221
00:13:51,041 --> 00:13:53,291
Daddy, I want it.

222
00:13:53,375 --> 00:13:54,958
[Arashiyama] I don't wanna hear it.

223
00:14:05,125 --> 00:14:06,500
I'm so sorry.

224
00:14:08,041 --> 00:14:09,125
Manami…

225
00:14:14,208 --> 00:14:15,250
[sobs]

226
00:14:15,333 --> 00:14:16,750
I'm sorry.

227
00:14:19,125 --> 00:14:21,250
ORGANIZED CRIME DIVISION

228
00:14:23,083 --> 00:14:25,500
- [Fukami] Detective, you got a minute?
- Sure. What is it?

229
00:14:26,083 --> 00:14:29,666
I asked Tonohata if he remembered anything
else about the day of the incident,

230
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:32,125
and what he said was interesting.

231
00:14:32,208 --> 00:14:33,041
Oh yeah?

232
00:14:33,125 --> 00:14:36,000
He had a plastic bag over his head,
so he couldn't tell where he was,

233
00:14:36,083 --> 00:14:40,333
but he heard a… compressor,
and he could smell oil.

234
00:14:40,416 --> 00:14:42,083
What do you think that could be?

235
00:14:42,166 --> 00:14:44,750
Compressor… oil?

236
00:14:46,458 --> 00:14:49,666
That could be an auto repair shop,
couldn't it?

237
00:14:51,000 --> 00:14:53,875
Hey, Arashiyama. A visitor for you.

238
00:14:57,583 --> 00:14:59,750
[Miho] Here. These are for you.

239
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:01,583
THANK YOU FOR YOUR HARD WORK!

240
00:15:03,125 --> 00:15:06,083
Thank you. That's very kind, Ms. Miho.

241
00:15:06,166 --> 00:15:10,583
Mr. Arashiyama,
I just wanted to say… I'm grateful to you.

242
00:15:11,291 --> 00:15:15,250
We're gonna go somewhere
that's better for raising kids.

243
00:15:16,083 --> 00:15:16,958
You're moving?

244
00:15:17,541 --> 00:15:18,458
Yeah.

245
00:15:19,375 --> 00:15:21,791
The time we've spent talking

246
00:15:21,875 --> 00:15:25,250
has helped me to see that
things could actually get better.

247
00:15:27,916 --> 00:15:29,416
Oh, okay.

248
00:15:42,583 --> 00:15:45,791
DATING APP SCAM CASE
INVESTIGATION MATERIALS

249
00:15:45,875 --> 00:15:47,875
[ominous music playing]

250
00:15:47,958 --> 00:15:50,000
[music transitions to jazz]

251
00:15:51,125 --> 00:15:52,666
[baby crying]

252
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:02,916
[banging on door]

253
00:16:18,625 --> 00:16:20,625
[baby cries intensely]

254
00:16:25,541 --> 00:16:26,958
[Miho] Mr. Arashiyama.

255
00:16:27,916 --> 00:16:29,166
What are you doing here?

256
00:16:32,875 --> 00:16:34,375
I was packing and…

257
00:16:35,125 --> 00:16:38,791
I found pictures of Manami,
so I thought I'd send them to you.

258
00:16:38,875 --> 00:16:41,333
Wait. Did something happen
with Manami's case?

259
00:16:43,416 --> 00:16:44,875
Open the door please.

260
00:16:51,458 --> 00:16:52,291
What happened--

261
00:16:52,875 --> 00:16:54,000
Miss Miho.

262
00:16:55,166 --> 00:16:57,500
You're under arrest
under suspicion of fraud.

263
00:16:57,583 --> 00:16:59,666
What? What are you--

264
00:17:00,625 --> 00:17:03,750
- What? Ow! That hurts! Ow!
- 7:20 a.m.

265
00:17:03,833 --> 00:17:04,916
In custody.

266
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:09,041
- Why would he arrest her himself?
- Arashiyama is a beast.

267
00:17:09,125 --> 00:17:10,666
[Miho] What's going on?

268
00:17:11,791 --> 00:17:14,666
As the arrest warrant states,
you are suspected of committing fraud.

269
00:17:14,750 --> 00:17:17,375
Why are you doing this to me?
I don't understand!

270
00:17:17,458 --> 00:17:18,833
[Fukami] Through our investigation,

271
00:17:18,916 --> 00:17:21,666
we found multiple complaints
of marriage fraud against you.

272
00:17:21,750 --> 00:17:22,750
We have reason to believe

273
00:17:22,833 --> 00:17:24,833
you intentionally deceived
more than one victim

274
00:17:24,916 --> 00:17:26,666
and that you did so for financial gain.

275
00:17:26,750 --> 00:17:28,541
[Miho] I don't know
what you're talking about!

276
00:17:28,625 --> 00:17:30,625
We'll question you
down at the station. Let's go.

277
00:17:30,708 --> 00:17:33,083
[Miho] Wait, wait, wait!
What about my baby?

278
00:17:33,166 --> 00:17:35,666
He'll die without me.
What kind of monsters are you?

279
00:17:35,750 --> 00:17:38,083
[Arashiyama] We've called social services.
Don't worry.

280
00:17:38,166 --> 00:17:40,833
I helped you with Manami's case, didn't I?
What are you doing?

281
00:17:40,916 --> 00:17:41,875
[man] Okay, get in.

282
00:17:41,958 --> 00:17:43,708
[Arashiyama] That has nothing to do
with this.

283
00:17:45,583 --> 00:17:48,208
We enforce the law, no matter what.

284
00:17:50,791 --> 00:17:52,916
We enforce the law.

285
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,416
[music fades]

286
00:17:55,333 --> 00:17:56,458
Mr. Kujo,

287
00:17:57,125 --> 00:18:00,208
Mr. Karasuma showed up here the other day.

288
00:18:00,916 --> 00:18:02,416
Mr. Karasuma came here?

289
00:18:02,500 --> 00:18:05,583
Yep. He told me off.
Said if I cared about you at all,

290
00:18:05,666 --> 00:18:06,958
I should stay away from you.

291
00:18:10,875 --> 00:18:12,291
Is that right?

292
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:22,208
Hello there.

293
00:18:22,833 --> 00:18:25,666
What's going on?
You plotting something with your lawyer?

294
00:18:27,041 --> 00:18:29,833
Hello, Detective. What can I do for you?

295
00:18:30,833 --> 00:18:32,458
I'm here as a customer.

296
00:18:32,541 --> 00:18:34,708
There's a little scratch on my car.

297
00:18:36,458 --> 00:18:37,500
Hey, Mibu.

298
00:18:38,541 --> 00:18:41,166
There have been a lot of violent incidents
around you lately.

299
00:18:41,250 --> 00:18:44,208
<i>The kidnapping and assault of Tonohata,</i>
<i>the call girl driver.</i>

300
00:18:44,791 --> 00:18:47,083
<i>A street assault,</i>
<i>blunt object to the head.</i>

301
00:18:47,166 --> 00:18:49,125
<i>And Kanemoto's drowning.</i>

302
00:18:49,625 --> 00:18:52,708
<i>Not to mention the murder committed by</i>
<i>one of your guys, Inukai, ten years ago.</i>

303
00:18:54,500 --> 00:18:57,416
Either you have really bad luck,
or you're involved.

304
00:19:00,875 --> 00:19:04,416
No offense,
but your shop's really starting to stink.

305
00:19:04,500 --> 00:19:05,583
[sniffing]

306
00:19:06,166 --> 00:19:09,458
Now, what is that?
Is it the stench of death?

307
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,125
[Mibu] Detective.

308
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,208
If that's the case,

309
00:19:17,291 --> 00:19:19,833
you might wanna go get your car fixed
somewhere else.

310
00:19:21,833 --> 00:19:24,250
Anyway,
I have the right to refuse your business.

311
00:19:24,333 --> 00:19:25,166
If it was up to me,

312
00:19:25,250 --> 00:19:27,791
criminals like you
wouldn't have any rights.

313
00:19:28,833 --> 00:19:34,583
Mr. Kujo, how do you sleep at night
protecting these depraved parasites?

314
00:19:35,541 --> 00:19:38,041
Lawyers don't protect people
who do evil things.

315
00:19:38,541 --> 00:19:40,375
We protect the justice system.

316
00:19:41,458 --> 00:19:44,166
The justice system? What do you mean?

317
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:46,500
I don't expect you to understand this,

318
00:19:46,583 --> 00:19:49,458
but without us,
our criminal justice system wouldn't work.

319
00:19:49,541 --> 00:19:52,708
So you being a Yakuza lapdog
is how you fight for justice?

320
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:54,875
All I'm saying is
the accused require a defense,

321
00:19:54,958 --> 00:19:56,666
and if I refuse,
another lawyer has to do it.

322
00:19:56,750 --> 00:19:59,583
That doesn't justify telling your clients
not to answer questions.

323
00:19:59,666 --> 00:20:01,083
You're supporting criminal activity.

324
00:20:01,166 --> 00:20:02,750
Last I looked, the right to remain silent

325
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:05,541
is enshrined in the Criminal Code
and the constitution.

326
00:20:05,625 --> 00:20:08,500
Maybe you need a refresher
on what our laws actually are?

327
00:20:13,333 --> 00:20:14,875
So, you're telling me…

328
00:20:17,458 --> 00:20:19,750
if your daughter was raped and murdered,

329
00:20:19,833 --> 00:20:22,916
you'd defend the perpetrators
because that's their right?

330
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,000
[upbeat music playing]

331
00:20:28,041 --> 00:20:30,541
As a lawyer,
my duty is to serve our justice system

332
00:20:30,625 --> 00:20:32,416
and defend people's rights.

333
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:33,625
To answer your question,

334
00:20:33,708 --> 00:20:35,333
I'd have to recuse myself from a case

335
00:20:35,416 --> 00:20:37,125
if my emotions might cloud my judgment.

336
00:20:38,458 --> 00:20:41,750
The police and defense lawyers
play different roles,

337
00:20:41,833 --> 00:20:44,000
but we all have the same goal.

338
00:20:44,083 --> 00:20:45,875
A peaceful society, right?

339
00:20:48,541 --> 00:20:51,958
Nice. The Yakuza's fixer
spouting philosophy.

340
00:20:53,166 --> 00:20:56,416
I'm making it my personal mission
to finish you, Kujo.

341
00:21:02,750 --> 00:21:04,916
If my daughter was the one
who was murdered,

342
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:08,166
I promise you there's no way in hell
I'd leave it to the courts.

343
00:21:08,250 --> 00:21:09,458
[music fades]

344
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:11,750
[Mrs. Karasuma] Aren't they beautiful?

345
00:21:12,625 --> 00:21:13,458
Huh?

346
00:21:14,166 --> 00:21:15,291
The flowers.

347
00:21:16,958 --> 00:21:18,416
Oh, did you go out and get those?

348
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:22,583
Mm-hmm. Not too far,
just past the train station.

349
00:21:23,916 --> 00:21:27,250
I saw these on my way there,
and I thought they looked so nice.

350
00:21:27,333 --> 00:21:28,333
You did, huh?

351
00:21:28,416 --> 00:21:29,416
Here.

352
00:21:29,500 --> 00:21:30,791
- Thank you.
- Mm-hmm.

353
00:21:34,708 --> 00:21:36,166
Omurice?

354
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:39,583
Whenever you needed cheering up,
this would always work.

355
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:42,041
I look like I need cheering up today?

356
00:21:42,583 --> 00:21:44,666
Well… Go ahead. Dig in.

357
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:48,208
Thank you very much.

358
00:21:53,041 --> 00:21:55,958
I made it myself,
but it's been awhile. How'd I do?

359
00:21:56,041 --> 00:21:56,916
[chuckles]

360
00:21:57,000 --> 00:21:57,833
It's so good.

361
00:21:57,916 --> 00:21:59,208
[chuckles]

362
00:21:59,291 --> 00:22:00,583
And nostalgic.

363
00:22:01,333 --> 00:22:03,250
I'd always eat this before exams,

364
00:22:03,333 --> 00:22:05,583
and every time,
it gave me the boost I needed.

365
00:22:09,458 --> 00:22:10,416
What is it, son?

366
00:22:14,083 --> 00:22:15,375
Just thinking.

367
00:22:15,458 --> 00:22:16,500
[Mrs. Karasuma] About what?

368
00:22:16,583 --> 00:22:17,625
By the way,

369
00:22:17,708 --> 00:22:20,333
I had the coffee you gave me
with Mr. Kujo the other day.

370
00:22:20,833 --> 00:22:22,291
He said it was delicious.

371
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:23,916
You know,

372
00:22:24,500 --> 00:22:27,666
I should go and say hello
to Mr. Kujo one of these days.

373
00:22:27,750 --> 00:22:28,625
[laughs]

374
00:22:29,666 --> 00:22:32,041
[laughing] No, it's okay.
That's not necessary.

375
00:22:32,916 --> 00:22:33,958
You should eat too, Mom.

376
00:22:34,041 --> 00:22:37,333
Mmm. I will. Just give me a minute.

377
00:22:38,416 --> 00:22:39,791
[bell dings]

378
00:22:44,083 --> 00:22:47,833
[Karasuma] We had omurice with Dad
before sports day at school, remember?

379
00:22:48,333 --> 00:22:50,750
He was so excited
for the father-son relay race.

380
00:22:52,041 --> 00:22:54,208
And thanks to your cooking,
we got first place.

381
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:56,916
Your dad used to say

382
00:22:58,125 --> 00:23:01,458
omurice is our family's luckiest dish.

383
00:23:03,291 --> 00:23:07,083
He said,
"I have an important business trip today."

384
00:23:10,833 --> 00:23:13,166
"So I want to have omurice."

385
00:23:15,708 --> 00:23:17,041
That morning…

386
00:23:19,125 --> 00:23:21,083
That was the last time.

387
00:23:21,166 --> 00:23:23,166
[melancholy music playing]

388
00:23:25,500 --> 00:23:26,583
Hey, Mom?

389
00:23:34,541 --> 00:23:35,583
Mom?

390
00:23:37,791 --> 00:23:40,000
He said he'd be back late that night.

391
00:23:41,458 --> 00:23:43,625
But I never thought that he wouldn't.

392
00:23:46,166 --> 00:23:47,875
He's never coming home.

393
00:23:48,666 --> 00:23:49,625
Never.

394
00:23:51,416 --> 00:23:52,625
And it isn't fair.

395
00:23:54,750 --> 00:23:57,750
Why would they write
those horrible things about your dad?

396
00:23:58,500 --> 00:23:59,916
[breathes shakily]

397
00:24:01,208 --> 00:24:02,833
[Mrs. Karasuma] <i>I was so scared.</i>

398
00:24:04,166 --> 00:24:06,250
<i>But no one helped us.</i>

399
00:24:07,250 --> 00:24:09,625
I didn't want to know those things.

400
00:24:09,708 --> 00:24:10,666
[sobs]

401
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:13,333
I wanted to remember the man we knew.

402
00:24:13,416 --> 00:24:15,041
You need to breathe.

403
00:24:15,125 --> 00:24:17,083
After your dad was gone,

404
00:24:18,625 --> 00:24:19,875
Shinji, I was…

405
00:24:19,958 --> 00:24:21,750
- Please, Mom, it's okay.
- You don't understand.

406
00:24:21,833 --> 00:24:23,000
- I promised him!
- I will not…

407
00:24:23,083 --> 00:24:23,916
[sobs]

408
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,333
…ever do anything
that would hurt you, okay?

409
00:24:35,666 --> 00:24:37,458
You said something before.

410
00:24:39,333 --> 00:24:43,041
That Dad always wanted me to help others.

411
00:24:47,125 --> 00:24:48,166
And I will.

412
00:24:50,083 --> 00:24:51,125
Don't worry.

413
00:24:52,958 --> 00:24:54,000
[music fades]

414
00:24:56,041 --> 00:24:57,083
See you soon.

415
00:24:58,541 --> 00:24:59,458
Shinji.

416
00:25:00,583 --> 00:25:02,500
I'd like to meet Mr. Kujo.

417
00:25:03,708 --> 00:25:04,625
[Karasuma] Mr. Kujo?

418
00:25:06,958 --> 00:25:09,000
He is the one who's making you suffer.

419
00:25:12,250 --> 00:25:13,708
I'll hold you to it, then.

420
00:25:35,791 --> 00:25:37,333
[Karasuma] Everyone, how's it going?

421
00:25:37,416 --> 00:25:39,000
[Yakushimae] Good. How are you?

422
00:25:40,708 --> 00:25:41,833
Mr. Karasuma.

423
00:25:41,916 --> 00:25:42,750
Yes?

424
00:25:43,916 --> 00:25:45,583
[Kujo] I found this on the floor.

425
00:25:45,666 --> 00:25:47,791
[ominous sting]

426
00:25:48,791 --> 00:25:50,375
[Karasuma] Oh, yeah. Thanks.

427
00:25:50,458 --> 00:25:52,958
- What's going on?
- Nothing. He found my pen.

428
00:25:53,041 --> 00:25:54,958
[Yakushimae] Is there something special
about it?

429
00:25:55,041 --> 00:25:56,375
[Karasuma] No! It's nothing!

430
00:25:58,166 --> 00:26:00,750
Anyway, what are doing here?
Slacking off again, Yakushimae?

431
00:26:01,500 --> 00:26:04,125
Speak for yourself, Mr. Karasuma.
I got here hours ago,

432
00:26:04,208 --> 00:26:05,458
so who's the real slacker?

433
00:26:05,541 --> 00:26:07,041
I stopped at my parents' house.

434
00:26:07,125 --> 00:26:09,833
[Yakushimae] Oh, that's sweet.
Fine, you get a pass.

435
00:26:09,916 --> 00:26:12,375
I think I'll take a break soon.
You wanna join me?

436
00:26:13,041 --> 00:26:15,583
We could have some of the coffee
your mother gave you the other day

437
00:26:15,666 --> 00:26:16,791
if you want.

438
00:26:17,833 --> 00:26:20,791
I told her that we tried it
and you said it was delicious.

439
00:26:20,875 --> 00:26:22,000
That made her happy.

440
00:26:22,083 --> 00:26:23,041
It's exquisite coffee.

441
00:26:25,083 --> 00:26:26,125
Mr. Kujo,

442
00:26:26,625 --> 00:26:29,583
my mother said she would…
like to meet you.

443
00:26:29,666 --> 00:26:31,625
She wants me to arrange a visit.

444
00:26:32,500 --> 00:26:33,416
A visit, huh?

445
00:26:33,500 --> 00:26:34,875
[Karasuma] She made me promise.

446
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:42,291
Well, one must always keep one's promises.

447
00:26:43,958 --> 00:26:45,041
Thank you very much.

448
00:26:45,541 --> 00:26:47,875
You could take them to a nice restaurant.

449
00:26:47,958 --> 00:26:50,541
There's a kaiseki one called Nomura.

450
00:26:50,625 --> 00:26:52,666
Nomura?
Isn't it hard to get a reservation there?

451
00:26:52,750 --> 00:26:54,708
- Yeah.
- No, that place is way too expensive.

452
00:26:54,791 --> 00:26:57,541
No, no, Mr. Karasuma.
I don't think you should worry about that.

453
00:26:57,625 --> 00:26:59,666
Why don't you come out with us,
Yakushimae?

454
00:26:59,750 --> 00:27:01,375
As a way to show my appreciation.

455
00:27:01,458 --> 00:27:02,291
That's okay.

456
00:27:02,375 --> 00:27:06,750
I'd rather not get treated to dinner
by anyone on the Yakuza payroll.

457
00:27:08,083 --> 00:27:10,791
I think you might be overstating
the situation a bit.

458
00:27:11,500 --> 00:27:12,791
Right, Mr. Karasuma?

459
00:27:12,875 --> 00:27:14,166
Yeah, I'd agree with that.

460
00:27:14,250 --> 00:27:19,333
You know, it's become really clear to me.
A bowl of gyudon bought with honest money,

461
00:27:19,416 --> 00:27:24,458
tastes so much better than the finest food
bought with dirty money ever could.

462
00:27:26,166 --> 00:27:28,416
I'm sure Black Thunder agrees with me.

463
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:32,583
Mr. Kujo, we should consider raising
our attorney fees.

464
00:27:34,250 --> 00:27:35,083
Why's that?

465
00:27:35,166 --> 00:27:38,250
Because by doing that,
we'd be free to say no to cases

466
00:27:38,333 --> 00:27:39,541
we don't want to take.

467
00:27:41,333 --> 00:27:44,875
I believe it's best to have a low,
fixed fee no matter who the client is.

468
00:27:45,458 --> 00:27:47,791
[Yakushimae] Because there are people
who are saved by that,

469
00:27:47,875 --> 00:27:50,375
and we don't choose
who is and isn't deserving.

470
00:27:50,458 --> 00:27:52,625
I've heard that so many times.

471
00:27:52,708 --> 00:27:54,875
I'm not changing how I run my firm.

472
00:27:55,583 --> 00:27:57,833
Greed and vanity will
be the death of us all.

473
00:27:57,916 --> 00:27:59,083
[Karasuma] Fair enough.

474
00:27:59,166 --> 00:28:01,916
I still think it's better
if we choose who we represent.

475
00:28:03,375 --> 00:28:07,166
You've started to speak up,
Mr. Karasuma. It's a good look.

476
00:28:08,083 --> 00:28:10,750
But Mr. Kujo won't listen to us anyway.

477
00:28:11,250 --> 00:28:13,583
Your mother might be able
to get through to him.

478
00:28:13,666 --> 00:28:15,166
No, no, no.

479
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:17,541
[cell phone buzzes]

480
00:28:20,458 --> 00:28:23,041
MR. KYOGOKU

481
00:28:38,041 --> 00:28:40,958
[Kyogoku] Sorry we have to meet
in a place like this.

482
00:28:43,500 --> 00:28:45,375
I guess this a cash-only hotel?

483
00:28:45,458 --> 00:28:48,875
Moldy, there's no windows,
and it has bad energy.

484
00:28:48,958 --> 00:28:50,333
It's really depressing.

485
00:28:51,208 --> 00:28:54,500
But, uh… it can't be avoided

486
00:28:54,583 --> 00:28:57,875
since Koyama's still in jail,
charged with fraud, of all things.

487
00:28:59,500 --> 00:29:01,541
It should only be a couple more weeks.

488
00:29:02,625 --> 00:29:03,458
[sighs]

489
00:29:04,041 --> 00:29:05,416
It's unbelievable.

490
00:29:06,208 --> 00:29:09,708
He gets charged with fraud because
I stayed at a hotel under his name?

491
00:29:09,791 --> 00:29:11,125
What the hell is that?

492
00:29:12,791 --> 00:29:17,000
Well, at least you fixed it
so he'll be cut loose in 20 days.

493
00:29:24,916 --> 00:29:27,958
So is there…
anything can I do for you today?

494
00:29:28,041 --> 00:29:29,875
[ominous music playing]

495
00:29:29,958 --> 00:29:32,958
The kids went out to do the collecting
as usual…

496
00:29:35,541 --> 00:29:40,083
and somehow the cops framed our boss
on conspiracy charges or something,

497
00:29:40,166 --> 00:29:41,833
while he's still in jail!

498
00:29:44,166 --> 00:29:47,458
It seemed like another unreasonable charge
for you to get rid of.

499
00:29:50,375 --> 00:29:52,791
This is Boss Fushimi
of the Fushimi-gumi gang?

500
00:29:52,875 --> 00:29:57,000
The cops…
are seriously trying to take us down.

501
00:30:00,041 --> 00:30:00,916
[grunts]

502
00:30:02,833 --> 00:30:03,833
Thing is,

503
00:30:05,083 --> 00:30:09,000
when I told the boss
about everything that you've done for us,

504
00:30:09,083 --> 00:30:10,916
he got really interested.

505
00:30:13,833 --> 00:30:17,458
Go see him. Hear what he has to say.

506
00:30:18,541 --> 00:30:20,541
[upbeat music playing]

507
00:30:21,458 --> 00:30:23,458
[indistinct chatter]

508
00:30:24,625 --> 00:30:26,500
Attorney Kujo, we'll drive you.

509
00:30:27,000 --> 00:30:27,833
No, it's okay.

510
00:30:27,916 --> 00:30:29,833
[henchman] The underboss told us
to drive you.

511
00:30:29,916 --> 00:30:31,458
[Kujo] I have my own car, thanks.

512
00:30:56,000 --> 00:30:58,291
You look like you have
something to say to me.

513
00:30:59,833 --> 00:31:01,375
Go ahead. What is it?

514
00:31:05,125 --> 00:31:07,291
You've made it as far as the big boss now.

515
00:31:09,375 --> 00:31:10,666
What are you planning to do?

516
00:31:12,791 --> 00:31:14,791
[cell phone buzzes]

517
00:31:21,125 --> 00:31:23,250
Hello. This is Kujo.

518
00:31:24,166 --> 00:31:25,416
[man] <i>Mr. Kujo,</i>

519
00:31:26,083 --> 00:31:30,375
<i>my name is Yamazaki from the Fusei-kai,</i>
<i>a branch of Fushimi-gumi.</i>

520
00:31:30,875 --> 00:31:34,875
<i>I'm calling because I heard</i>
<i>you're handling Mr. Kyogoku's defense.</i>

521
00:31:36,250 --> 00:31:37,708
[Kujo] What can I do for you?

522
00:31:38,208 --> 00:31:40,458
[Yamazaki] <i>One of our members</i>
<i>was arrested for robbery.</i>

523
00:31:40,541 --> 00:31:42,375
<i>I'm wondering if you can help.</i>

524
00:31:44,875 --> 00:31:47,583
We shouldn't discuss this on the phone.
You'd better come to my office.

525
00:31:48,208 --> 00:31:50,166
[Yamazaki] <i>Okay. Thank you very much.</i>

526
00:32:15,500 --> 00:32:16,791
Mr. Karasuma.

527
00:32:17,875 --> 00:32:18,750
[music fades]

528
00:32:18,833 --> 00:32:22,125
We have to go eat Japan's number one
takoyaki before heading back.

529
00:32:26,583 --> 00:32:30,208
Mr. Kujo, do you not get what's going on?

530
00:32:34,083 --> 00:32:36,833
We should take on cases
that could set legal precedent.

531
00:32:37,458 --> 00:32:39,500
But instead, to be honest, Mr. Kujo,

532
00:32:39,583 --> 00:32:41,625
you're at the beck and call
of a bunch of gangsters.

533
00:32:43,625 --> 00:32:44,833
Beck and call?

534
00:32:47,125 --> 00:32:49,291
Being involved in our recent cases,

535
00:32:49,375 --> 00:32:52,041
it's given me insight
on how the Yakuza treat each other.

536
00:32:53,375 --> 00:32:54,416
Let's hear it.

537
00:32:56,416 --> 00:32:58,208
They don't give a shit about each other.

538
00:32:58,708 --> 00:33:01,500
There's nothing they wouldn't do
to protect themselves.

539
00:33:03,291 --> 00:33:04,708
They're going to betray you.

540
00:33:06,250 --> 00:33:08,250
[tense music playing]

541
00:33:12,041 --> 00:33:14,041
[Mibu] I heard Inukai's out.

542
00:33:14,125 --> 00:33:18,791
[Kuga] Yup. A guy working security
at a club in Roppongi saw him.

543
00:33:18,875 --> 00:33:20,875
Why didn't he give me a call?

544
00:33:23,666 --> 00:33:26,750
There's some rumors going on about him.
They don't sound good.

545
00:33:38,666 --> 00:33:40,208
[man] It's been a while.

546
00:33:40,791 --> 00:33:41,750
Sure has.

547
00:33:41,833 --> 00:33:46,333
Your guy, Ayabe, he, uh,
looked out for me when I was in juvie.

548
00:33:47,750 --> 00:33:50,291
Juvenile prison's tough enough

549
00:33:50,375 --> 00:33:53,125
without someone looking out for you
in there.

550
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:59,583
When Mibu turned his back on you,
it must've been hell.

551
00:34:00,625 --> 00:34:02,041
You could say that.

552
00:34:02,541 --> 00:34:03,500
Just did.

553
00:34:07,750 --> 00:34:09,250
Mibu must be on your list.

554
00:34:11,583 --> 00:34:12,583
Yeah.

555
00:34:13,083 --> 00:34:16,083
Because of Mibu, I lost ten years
for just three million yen.

556
00:34:20,041 --> 00:34:23,416
You've got it out for him too,
don't you Mr. Sugawara?

557
00:34:23,500 --> 00:34:24,750
I heard all about it.

558
00:34:26,875 --> 00:34:29,708
That your nursing home thing
was going great

559
00:34:30,875 --> 00:34:32,750
until he ruined everything for you.

560
00:34:37,041 --> 00:34:39,666
Let's go take Mibu's 300 million yen.

561
00:34:40,250 --> 00:34:42,041
[dramatic sting]

562
00:34:45,541 --> 00:34:47,583
We'll kill him if he doesn't let us.

563
00:34:55,125 --> 00:34:56,750
Hell yeah.

564
00:34:59,458 --> 00:35:01,458
[upbeat music playing]

565
00:35:03,375 --> 00:35:04,458
Mr. Kujo.

566
00:35:05,958 --> 00:35:08,541
Please refuse to represent Boss Fushimi.

567
00:35:09,708 --> 00:35:11,416
You have to draw the line.

568
00:35:22,166 --> 00:35:23,458
If that's something you can't do…

569
00:35:27,083 --> 00:35:29,250
I won't be able to work with you anymore.

570
00:35:36,958 --> 00:35:40,458
[footsteps echo]

571
00:35:40,541 --> 00:35:42,125
[music fades]

572
00:35:49,541 --> 00:35:51,583
[closing theme song playing]

573
00:38:26,916 --> 00:38:28,583
[music fades]
